 June 05, 2025  

Are you a journalist with a critical perspective and a knack for uncovering untold stories in medicine or medical research? Have you identified emerging trends or observed how research influences (or fails to influence) clinical practice? Do you have insights into treatment — or mistreatment — that physicians should know? 

If so, Medscape wants to hear from you. 

We invite you to pitch your story, aimed at engaging our core audience of physicians and other healthcare professionals, to submissions@medscape.net. 

We are on the lookout for timely and engaging stories that reflect the practice of medicine. This includes everything from innovative patient care solutions to the everyday challenges faced by clinicians, including issues like workplace mistreatment. 

We welcome a variety of formats, such as:

All pitches should present an angle relevant to physicians and healthcare professionals. While not mandatory, including a news hook can enhance your pitch. 

Payment varies on the basis of complexity of the article. Our fees are project-based and competitive with industry standards. 

Journalists are also encouraged to express interest in covering breaking news, journal studies, and presentations at medical conferences. These assignments are not pitched and instead are assigned by our editorial team. Ideally, journalists should have experience writing for a clinical audience and possess a critical approach to research. 

Journal-based articles generally range from 500 to 800 words, with turnaround times from same-day to 3 days. Some pieces will require insights from the original researcher and an independent expert. 

Conference coverage may require travel and entails a same-day or next-day turnaround. 

