"https://news.google.com/rss/search?q=atp+tennis","Preview: Alcaraz peaking for Musetti matchup in Roland Garros SFs","https://www.atptour.com/en/news/alcaraz-musetti-roland-garros-2025-sf-preview","Thu, 05 Jun 2025 03:49:36 GMT","

Carlos Alcaraz and Lorenzo Musetti have already met twice this season on the ATP Masters 1000 stage, with the Spaniard victorious in the Monte-Carlo final and the Rome semis. The Spaniard now seeks his sixth consecutive Lexus ATP Head2Head win against Musetti in the Roland Garros semi-finals.

The defending champion at the clay-court major, Alcaraz enters Friday's match in peak form. After battling through a trio of four-setters in Paris, Alcaraz played his best match of the fortnight in the quarter-finals to dismiss Tommy Paul with the loss of just five games. The No. 2 player in the PIF ATP Rankings has not enjoyed such a dominant victory at Roland Garros since the opening round of his 2024 title run.

""I could close my eyes and everything went in,"" said Alcaraz, who did not face a break point behind an 89 per cent win rate on first serve, according to Infosys Stats. ""My feeling today was unbelievable. I was trying to hit every shot at 100 per cent, not thinking about anything else, but just hitting. Today was one of those matches when everything just went in.""

That such a performance came against Paul, who is set for a new career high after moving up to No. 8 in the PIF ATP Live Rankings, adds an air of invincibility for the Spaniard. But Musetti began Roland Garros at a career-high PIF ATP Ranking of No. 7 and is up to No. 6 in the Live Rankings. He would move to No. 4 with a semi-final victory.

The Italian has not beaten Alcaraz since their first meeting in 2022, a three-set thriller in the Hamburg final. Beginning with their ensuing meeting, at Roland Garros in 2023, Alcaraz has dropped just one set in six wins.



















































































