"https://news.google.com/rss/search?q=site:entertainmentnow.com","Latest Update on Kroy Biermann","https://entertainmentnow.com/bravo/kroy-biermann-update-kim-zolciak-divorce/","Thu, 05 Jun 2025 16:22:25 GMT","

You have to admit, Kroy Biermann has led a pretty interesting life. First, he played in the NFL for eight seasons, and then he married Kim Zolciak and starred with her on the “Real Housewives of Atlanta” for two full seasons before dropping to recurring status.

The ex-couple's fights played out very publicly for years, until Kroy decided to step back from the limelight. Kroy now works as a Crane and Rigging Coordinator, and according to his daughter, Ariana Biermann, in a new interview with The Daily Dish, he is living on his own.

After years of chaos and police calls, Kroy Biermann and Kim Zolciak finally called it quits in May 2023, with both filing for divorce. Now, two years later, it's their daughter, Ariana Biermann, who is providing a little bit of an update on what the ex-NFL player is up to.

She is a cast member of the brand-new Bravo series “The Next Gen NYC” and revealed how her dad has been doing amid his divorce from her mom, Kim Zolciak.

Ariana first admitted to The Daily Dish that she “doesn't know” how her dad has been, saying, “I haven't spoken to him in a little bit.” he then said that Kroy, who legally adopted her and her older sister, Brielle Biermann, in 2013, had been trying to call her so she believed that she would be “speaking to him soon.”

Kroy Biermann and Kim Zolciak spent many months fighting over their million-dollar mansion located in Georgia. According to People, the property sold for $2.75 million in January 2025, less than half of its original $6 million asking price

Ariana says that since the property is no longer an issue, Kroy is now living on his own. “I hope he's doing amazing,” she said while pondering the implications of the divorce on her entire family. “I think it's really a tough situation right now, between the family, and it goes through its waves,” she admitted. “I hope he's happy. I'm doing great.”

According to Kroy's new job description, he oversees logistics and helps with improving workplace efficiency. He started the position back in March 2024, and in May 2024, Superior Rigging and Erecting Co. shared a post on Instagram naming him the “Rockstar of the Month.”



